  "Message": "feat (provider/klingai): initial klingai provider (#12311)\n\n## Background\n\nThis PR adds a new provider for KlingAI, a service that offers motion control video generation capabilities. The integration allows users to generate videos by transferring motion from a reference video to a character in an image.\n\n## Summary\n\nAdded a new `@ai-sdk/klingai` package that implements the KlingAI provider with support for motion control video generation. The implementation includes:\n\n- Authentication via JWT tokens\n- Video generation API integration\n- Support for both standard and professional quality modes\n- Customizable watermarking and audio options\n- Comprehensive error handling and polling for async generation\n- Example usage in the AI functions demo\n\n## Manual Verification\n\nTested the KlingAI provider with both standard and professional mode configurations. Verified that the provider correctly:\n\n- Generates authentication tokens\n- Submits video generation tasks\n- Polls for task completion\n- Returns properly formatted video URLs\n- Handles errors appropriately\n\n## Checklist\n\n- [x] Tests have been added / updated (for bug fixes / features)\n- [x] Documentation has been added / updated (for bug fixes / features)\n- [x] A _patch_ changeset for relevant packages has been added (for bug fixes / features - run `pnpm changeset` in the project root)\n- [x] I have reviewed this pull request (self-review)\n\n## Future Work\n\n- Add more comprehensive documentation in the README\n- Support additional KlingAI video generation models as they become available",
  "Tags": [],
  "Fingerprint": "cc12a89ffbeb39c60541dee50d93bfac14a5602e:examples/ai-functions/.env.example:generic-api-key:22"
 },
